Tasks

Start a container named my-container, based on the nginx image.
  docker run -d --name my-container nginx
View the logs of the my-container container.
  docker logs my-container
Stop the container named my-container.
  docker stop my-container
Start a container named my-shell-container, based on the ubuntu image. The container should remain running in the background.
  docker run -d --name my-shell-container ubuntu sleep infinity
  docker exec my-shell-container echo "Hello Worold"
Stop and remove the container named my-shell-container.
  docker stop my-shell-container
  docker rm my-shell-container
